item.title: Under Armour partners with IBM Watson on artificial intelligence-based coaching
item.description:
Under Armour partners with IBM Watson on artificial intelligence-based coaching

Under Armour plans to add artificial intelligence to fitness tracking with the help of IBM Watson, creating virtual coaching for athletes. The sports apparel brand unveiled a collection of wearable technology products earlier this week to go with its tracking app, UA Record, including a smart shoe.

Under Armour Game Primer: Rankings, Commits & Top Storylines

Players suiting up in the ninth annual Under Armour All-American Game begin heading to the Sunshine State this coming Sunday and Monday in preparation for the game in Orlando on Jan. 2. All rankings are according to the 247Sports Composite Alabama (4): The nation's No. 3 running back B.J. Emmons.

item.title: Athos High-tech Biometric Fitness Clothing | OCR Europe
item.description:
Athos High-tech Biometric Fitness Clothing | OCR Europe

If you're looking for exercises and workout routines, there are plenty of apps that can download for free which would help you with that. But what about making sure that you're exercising properly? How do you know you're not working the wrong part of the body, favoring one side over the other, or doing anything else that might lead to an ineffective workout or even injury?
